On Fri, Jan 27, 2012 at 4:13 PM, Sebastien Lambla &lt;seb@...&gt; wrote:

&gt;   Seeing link tags (and headers) with URI templates in them made me throw
&gt; up in my mouth a little bit.
&gt;

Ok.

The if-match parameter could be called anything it&#39;s just a token that&#39;s
needed to keep the request idempotent. The subset resource is not being
retrieved so the client won&#39;t have an ETag for it.. I guess you could just
use the ETag from the collection and stick a corresponding If-Match in the
PUT request to the subset. Is that what you are getting at? It&#39;s definitely
easier from the clients point of view if it&#39;s just stuck in the URI, plus I
don&#39;t think it matters that much in this instance.. perhaps you can expand
on the problems it would cause?

As for URI templates in a link - a client of the app will know it is
dealing with a URI template because it&#39;s accessing the &#39;subset&#39; relation..
what&#39;s the issue there?

Apologies for upsetting your stomach, once you&#39;ve got yourself together
please could you expand a bit on what the actual issues are?

Cheers,
Mike


